winners of the award last year.

Each year, there are up to ﬁve recipi-
ents of the award. Each receives $2,500
and has his or her name inscribed on a
plaque displayed in the ‘William Pitt
Union.

According to Robert Houston, chair-
man of the awards committee, the plaque
will be featured next to the three plaques
commemorating winners of each award:
the Chancellor’s Distinguished Teaching’

Award, Research Award and Public

Service Award. -

1 Any full-time or part-time University
employee, excluding faculty, is eligible for
the award, provided they have been in ser-
vice for at least three years.

Employees at Pitt’s satellite campuses,
are also eligible for the award. In past
years, there has been a winner from the
Greensburg campus, as well as a nominee
from the J ohnstown campus.

Neither Rud nor 'Liebmann thought
that anyone had noticed their volunteer
eﬂorts prior to receiving the award.-

As Rud put it, “It’s not something I do
