.must display “service excellence in the

workplace,” as well as “a consistent pat-
tern of voluntary services of signiﬁcant
importance to the University community,
the local community, and/or professional ‘
organizations.”

The candidate must also have
“enhanced the reputation and prestige of '
the University of Pittsburgh regionally,
nationally, or intemationally.” A

“I consider that really part of my job
here,” Liebmarm said of his efforts meet-
ing these standards. .

Liebrnann volunteers as a youth advi-
sor at First Unitarian Church in Shadyside
and said he uses his-knowledge to train
other youth advisors throughout the.
United States.

He also uses his job skills to help
Woodland Hills School District with their
academic planning. , _

Liebmann said he feels that the award
program is important because it “helps
make staff more well-rounded,” and helps
them to “realize their full potential.” .

While Liebmann and Rud were both
nominated by -colleagues who work -in
their offices, nominations are open to all
members of the University community,
including students and alumni. '

